article.headline: Miami (Ohio) beats Kent State 31-6
article.description: Gus Ragland threw for a touchdown and ran for another on Saturday to help Miami of Ohio beat Kent State 31-6.

images.name: Young takes direct snap for short TD run
images.caption: Miami (OH) running back Kenny Young gets into the end zone with ease from the 2-yard line on a direct snap.

video.headline: Young takes direct snap for short TD run
video.caption: Miami (OH) running back Kenny Young gets into the end zone with ease from the 2-yard line on a direct snap.
video.title: Young takes direct snap for short TD run
video.description: Miami (OH) running back Kenny Young gets into the end zone with ease from the 2-yard line on a direct snap.

article.story: OXFORD, Ohio -- Gus Ragland threw for a touchdown and ran for another on Saturday to help Miami of Ohio beat Kent State 31-6. Kenny Young ran for 90 yards and a touchdown and caught three passes for 47 yards for the RedHawks (3-4, 3-1 Mid-American Conference). Ragland capped an 11-play, 98-yard drive with a 3-yard keeper to open the scoring on the first play of the second quarter. Young scored on a 2-yard run and Ragland's 2-yard pass to Luke Mayock made it 21-0 before the end of the first half. Jaylon Bester scored on a 6-yard run for his first career touchdown and Samuel Sloman capped Miami's scoring with a 42-yard field goal in the middle of the third quarter. Woody Barrett passed for 149 yards and ran for 75. His 7-yard TD run helped the Golden Flashes (1-6, 0-3) avoid a shutout with 36 seconds left in the game.

videos.headline: Bester plunges in 6-yard TD
videos.description: Miami (OH) running back Jaylon Bester finds the end zone from 6 yards out to extend the RedHawks' lead to 28-0 over Kent State.
